Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.28,0:00:12.22,Chn,,0,0,0,,请出示票据\N{\rEng}Tickets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.36,0:00:19.63,Chn,,0,0,0,,服务员 给我的同伴倒杯酒\N{\rEng}Barkeep. A drink for my colleague.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.63,0:00:20.76,Chn,,0,0,0,,我认识你么\N{\rEng}Do I know you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.76,0:00:22.49,Chn,,0,0,0,,我知道坐火车出行的唯一原因\N{\rEng}I know the only reason to travel by train
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:23.90,Chn,,0,0,0,,就是便于带武器\N{\rEng}is to travel with weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.90,0:00:26.23,Chn,,0,0,0,,而我们都知道 这旅途的尽头\N{\rEng}And we all know that at the end of this line,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.23,0:00:28.43,Chn,,0,0,0,,只有一种生物值得被杀死\N{\rEng}there's only one creature worth killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.44,0:00:31.37,Chn,,0,0,0,,那个穿白大褂的人\N{\rEng}The man in the white coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.37,0:00:33.97,Chn,,0,0,0,,不如轮流交流些故事\N{\rEng}May as well take turns exchanging stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.98,0:00:37.78,Chn,,0,0,0,,我的是在Ramamama星球开始的\N{\rEng}Mine begins on planet Ramamama.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.78,0:00:39.91,Chn,,0,0,0,,把他降进酸水里\N{\rEng}Lower him into acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.91,0:00:44.05,Chn,,0,0,0,,等他溶化了 再把别人降进酸水里\N{\rEng}Once he's dissolved, lower someone else into acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.05,0:00:45.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,他溶化了吗\N{\rEng}Is he dissolved?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.85,0:00:48.79,Chn,,0,0,0,,至少要利用停机时间重置降酸器吧\N{\rEng}At least use the downtime to reset the acid lowerer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.79,0:00:50.92,Chn,,0,0,0,,我真不喜欢你们的态度\N{\rEng}I really don't like the attitude around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.92,0:00:53.79,Chn,,0,0,0,,一种很“降我入酸”的态度\N{\rEng}It's a very "lower me into acid" attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.93,0:00:57.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,你是谁\N{\rEng}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.13,0:00:59.60,Chn,,0,0,0,,你是怎么进到我的圣殿的\N{\rEng}How did you reach my sanctum?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.60,0:01:02.07,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 问也是白问\N{\rEng}All right, this is going in circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:03.94,Chn,,0,0,0,,抓住他\N{\rEng}Seize him!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.02,0:01:22.15,Chn,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rEng}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.16,0:01:24.69,Chn,,0,0,0,,现在我来和你打\N{\rEng}Now I will fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:27.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,总之 他讲的故事是另一个版本\N{\rEng}Anyway, he tells a different version of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:29.29,Chn,,0,0,0,,我在此处开始哭什么的\N{\rEng}where I start crying or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.30,0:01:31.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,所以他必须得死\N{\rEng}That's why he has to die,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.37,0:01:32.83,Chn,,0,0,0,,因为他是个骗子\N{\rEng}'cause he's a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.83,0:01:34.03,Chn,,0,0,0,,所以\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.04,0:01:36.17,Chn,,0,0,0,,你为什么要杀了Rick Sanchez\N{\rEng}Why are you going to kill Rick Sanchez?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.17,0:01:37.30,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 我不知道那是谁\N{\rEng}Okay, I don't know who that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.30,0:01:41.04,Chn,,0,0,0,,我接受不了你这怪异的逻辑跳跃 让火车上的所有人都要去杀同一个人\N{\rEng}I don't accept your weird leap in logic that has everyone on a train going to kill one guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.04,0:01:45.78,Chn,,0,0,0,,就算我也要杀 我们又为何轮流讲出来呢 跟小女孩儿们通宵讲故事似的\N{\rEng}And even if I did, why would we take turns telling stories about it like little girls at a sleepover?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.78,0:01:47.45,Chn,,0,0,0,,如果你想伤人的话\N{\rEng}If you're trying to be hurtful,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.45,0:01:48.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,你做得很好\N{\rEng}you're doing a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.85,0:01:49.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,我来接着说吧\N{\rEng}I'll take his turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.85,0:01:51.98,Chn,,0,0,0,,说说我为什么要杀了Rick Sanchez\N{\rEng}Here's why I'm going to kill Rick Sanchez.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.99,0:01:53.39,Chn,,0,0,0,,你们几个慢慢聊\N{\rEng}You guys have fun with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.39,0:01:55.05,Chn,,0,0,0,,一个溶化成蛤蜊状的太阳\N{\rEng}Dissolve to a clam-shaped sun
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:56.92,Chn,,0,0,0,,在广袤的沙滩上升起\N{\rEng}rising over a giant beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.39,0:02:03.40,Chn,,0,0,0,,等到那时 他给我们孢子巢里的每一个人都留下了玩具和血肉\N{\rEng}By then, of course, he had left toys and flesh drops for every one of us in the spore-hive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.40,0:02:04.60,Chn,,0,0,0,,啊 来新人了\N{\rEng}Ah, a newcomer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.60,0:02:06.07,Chn,,0,0,0,,你是不是有个更好的\N{\rEng}I suppose you think you have a better story
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.07,0:02:08.87,Chn,,0,0,0,,Rick Sanchez拯救太空圣诞节的故事呢\N{\rEng}about how Rick Sanchez saved space Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:11.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,怎么会对Rick Sanchez如此痴迷\N{\rEng}What is with the Rick Sanchez obsession?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:14.54,Chn,,0,0,0,,我想对此最好的答案\N{\rEng}I think the best way to answer that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.54,0:02:17.14,Chn,,0,0,0,,是我的圣诞Rick故事\N{\rEng}is with my Christmas Rick tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.68,0:02:21.48,Chn,,0,0,0,,今晚本可以用鲁道夫的\N{\rEng}Could've used Rudolph tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.48,0:02:23.28,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 谢天谢地 我还不算太晚\N{\rEng}Oh, thank god. I'm not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.28,0:02:24.68,Chn,,0,0,0,,不知道该怎么谢你 Goomby\N{\rEng}I don't know how to thank you, Goomby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.69,0:02:25.75,Chn,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\rEng}No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.75,0:02:27.15,Chn,,0,0,0,,你只要进屋去好好玩就好了\N{\rEng}You just go in there and have a nice time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.15,0:02:28.82,Chn,,0,0,0,,会的 谢啦\N{\rEng}I will. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.90,0:02:35.09,Chn,,0,0,0,,圣诞快乐 Goomby\N{\rEng}Merry Christmas, Goomby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.10,0:02:36.96,Chn,,0,0,0,,圣诞快乐 Rick\N{\rEng}Merry Christmas, Rick.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:39.57,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 没关系\N{\rEng}Oh, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:40.97,Chn,,0,0,0,,我不是非得 对不起 我不应该\N{\rEng}I-I don't have to. Sorry if that was --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.97,0:02:42.37,Chn,,0,0,0,,不 我可以问下\N{\rEng}No. Um, um, I can ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.37,0:02:43.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,不不不 我不想成为一个负担\N{\rEng}No, no, no, I don't wanna be a burden.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.64,0:02:45.24,Chn,,0,0,0,,哦 好吧 是啊 是因为\N{\rEng}Oh, okay. Yeah, yeah, there's just --
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.24,0:02:46.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,人挺多的 家人 你知道吗\N{\rEng}There's a lot of people. Family. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:47.51,Chn,,0,0,0,,我都懂\N{\rEng}I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:48.77,Chn,,0,0,0,,- 你不生气 - 完全没问题\N{\rEng}-You're not mad? -Totally fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.78,0:02:50.11,Chn,,0,0,0,,拜拜\N{\rEng}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:58.12,Chn,,0,0,0,,这 好吧 不关我的事\N{\rEng}That -- okay, none of my business,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:02:59.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,但他在这个故事里并没有拯救圣诞节啊\N{\rEng}but he didn't even save Christmas in that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.85,0:03:00.72,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 你竟敢\N{\rEng}Oh, how dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.72,0:03:02.19,Chn,,0,0,0,,这并不意味着我对这些故事感兴趣\N{\rEng}That doesn't mean I'm invested.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.19,0:03:03.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,说出你的圣诞Rick故事\N{\rEng}Tell your Christmas Rick story!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.59,0:03:05.66,Chn,,0,0,0,,退后 后退\N{\rEng}Step the hell back! Back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.00,0:03:12.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,你要是想讲关于Rick Sanchez的故事\N{\rEng}You start teeing up a Rick Sanchez vignette,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:14.47,Chn,,0,0,0,,先吃我两颗子弹再说\N{\rEng}and you'll be doing it through two holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.47,0:03:16.34,Chn,,0,0,0,,我只是想弄清楚这列火车是怎么回事\N{\rEng}I'm just trying to figure out what's going on with this train.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:17.67,Chn,,0,0,0,,你对怎么上的车有印象吗\N{\rEng}Do you remember getting on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.67,0:03:20.47,Chn,,0,0,0,,没有 我能想起最早的事是\N{\rEng}No. First thing I remember is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.47,0:03:22.44,Chn,,0,0,0,,请出示票据\N{\rEng}Tickets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.41,0:03:26.81,Chn,,0,0,0,,那 你为什么要和Rick Sanchez约会\N{\rEng}So, why did you date Rick Sanchez?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:27.95,Chn,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.95,0:03:29.55,Chn,,0,0,0,,哦 你不必假装没跟他约会过\N{\rEng}Oh, you don't have to pretend you didn't date him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.55,0:03:31.35,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们都跟他约会过 我们懂的\N{\rEng}We all did. We get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.35,0:03:35.02,Chn,,0,0,0,,生命中的低谷 想忘掉前任 等等\N{\rEng}Low point in your life, rebound from an ex, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.02,0:03:36.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,没有 真没 那是谁\N{\rEng}No, really, who?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:38.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 可说呢\N{\rEng}oh, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:42.56,Chn,,0,0,0,,事实上 听着 当他见到我的家人时\N{\rEng}In fact, and get this, when he met my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.30,0:03:47.50,Chn,,0,0,0,,Leah Leah 过来看呀\N{\rEng}Leah! Leah, check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.50,0:03:48.70,Chn,,0,0,0,,你在哪里认识的这个\N{\rEng}Where'd you meet this, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:50.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,调皮鬼\N{\rEng}...Sprite?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.64,0:03:52.84,Chn,,0,0,0,,他实际上是个人类\N{\rEng}He's actually a human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.84,0:03:55.37,Chn,,0,0,0,,但他发明了传送技术\N{\rEng}But he invented portal tech?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.31,Chn,,0,0,0,,我就是时间的概念\N{\rEng}I am the concept of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.31,0:03:58.44,Chn,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\rEng}Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:03:59.71,Chn,,0,0,0,,我警告过你不要讲\N{\rEng}I warned you not to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.71,0:04:01.65,Chn,,0,0,0,,- 我不是故意的 - 你都不需要故意\N{\rEng}-I wasn't trying. -You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.65,0:04:04.45,Chn,,0,0,0,,这列火车明显在强化并且关联起不相关的叙事段落\N{\rEng}The train is obviously amplifying and linking unrelated narrative fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.79,0:04:07.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,Morty 我告诉过你 如果你再找到我\N{\rEng}Morty? I told you if you found me again,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.59,0:04:09.19,Chn,,0,0,0,,要亮明身份\N{\rEng}identify yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:10.86,Chn,,0,0,0,,我不知道是你\N{\rEng}I didn't know it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.86,0:04:12.06,Chn,,0,0,0,,你怎么会认不出我呢\N{\rEng}How did you not recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:13.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,这套伪装不是你造的吗\N{\rEng}Didn't you create the disguises?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.59,0:04:15.39,Chn,,0,0,0,,我造出的东西当然要管用 Morty\N{\rEng}When I create shit, it works, Morty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.40,0:04:16.73,Chn,,0,0,0,,这就是有才华\N{\rEng}It's called being talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.73,0:04:17.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,为什么我们找不到发动机\N{\rEng}Why can't we find the engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.80,0:04:20.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,这不是真正的火车 而是一个故事机器\N{\rEng}It's not a real train, it's a story device.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:22.47,Chn,,0,0,0,,就是字面的意思 字面意义下的文字机器\N{\rEng}Literally. A literal literary device
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.47,0:04:24.87,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们简直逐字逐句比喻般地身处其中\N{\rEng}quite literally metaphorically containing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.87,0:04:25.67,Chn,,0,0,0,,是套模拟\N{\rEng}A simulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.67,0:04:27.27,Chn,,0,0,0,,更糟 是本选集\N{\rEng}Worse. An anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.27,0:04:28.94,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我们怎么劫持它\N{\rEng}Okay, so how -- how do we hijack it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.94,0:04:31.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 Morty 它已经被劫持至少有两分钟了\N{\rEng}Oh, Morty, it's been hijacked for at least two full minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.88,0:04:33.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,你没听到这些错乱的对话吗\N{\rEng}Are you not hearing this insane conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.88,0:04:36.35,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 请出示票据男 停下这个选集\N{\rEng}Okay, tickets please guy, stop the anthology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.35,0:04:38.68,Chn,,0,0,0,,如果要做特辑的话 我们会做跨维度有线电视的\N{\rEng}If we wanted one-offs, we'd do interdimensional cable,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.69,0:04:40.62,Chn,,0,0,0,,而不是这种拘谨的 过度描绘的\N{\rEng}Not some uptight, overwritten --
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:42.29,Chn,,0,0,0,,- Rick - 该死的\N{\rEng}Rick? God damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.29,0:04:43.49,Chn,,0,0,0,,请出示票据\N{\rEng}Tickets, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.49,0:04:44.69,Chn,,0,0,0,,老兄 我觉得你应该\N{\rEng}Dude, I'm sure you've got, like,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.69,0:04:46.63,Chn,,0,0,0,,已经有很多很多票了吧\N{\rEng}so many tickets at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:48.83,Chn,,0,0,0,,我的天啊 请出示票据男也太壮了\N{\rEng}Jesus! The tickets please guy is cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.83,0:04:50.76,Chn,,0,0,0,,他的那个\N{\rEng}He -- he -- he's -- he's got those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.76,0:04:52.70,Chn,,0,0,0,,怎么说的来着 人鱼线就像精槽一样\N{\rEng}W-what do you call them. Uhm, cum gutters.
